Nigerian gospel singer, Frank Edwards, has confirmed the reports that the Nigerian musician, Sister Osinachi Nwachukwu, was murdered by her husband. Recall that the singer was announced dead on Friday, after being on life support for the past two months. According to reports gathered, it was alleged that husband who has been constantly physically assaulting her for years, recently beat her till she fell into coma. Edwards in a post via his Instagram page on Saturday confirmed the reports, stating that an unreasonable human put off the Ekwueme crooner’s shining light. He wrote, “So that Unreasonable human being finally put off a shining lightz I won’t say much now. “I’ll let the former Nddc director ( AUNTY Joy ) who did everything possible to stop this from happening talk 1st, but it still happened koi we tried to stop this.”